{"fixed_xml":"<file name="line_18.json">
  <ITEM>
    In denen Thurneysischen Buchläden allhier, seynd dato folgende zwey Bücher zu haben, so in Nancy durch Subscriptiones gedruckt worden.
    <BIBL>
      <TITLE>Dictionnaire Universel- Francois & Latin, Vulgairement appelé Dictionaire de Trevoux</TITLE>, avec des Remarques d'Erudition & de Critique
      <VOLUME>5. Tom.</VOLUME>
      <FORMAT>fol.</FORMAT>
      <YEAR>1741</YEAR>; davon die 3. ersten Tom. dato schon zu beziehen sind; das gantze Werck kostet samt der Fracht
      <PRICE>fl. 24</PRICE>
    </BIBL>.
    <BIBL>
      <TITLE>Dictionaire Oeconomique, continant les moyens d'Augmenter son bien & de conserver sa santé</TITLE>, par
      <AUTHOR>Mister Noel Chomel</AUTHOR>, Augmenté d'un Nouveau Supplement de deux Volumes, par
      <AUTHOR>F. Marset, Doct. en Medecines</AUTHOR>.
      <FORMAT>avec fig.</FORMAT>
      <VOLUME>4. Tom.</VOLUME>
      <FORMAT>fol.</FORMAT>
      <YEAR>1741</YEAR>; davon der erste Tomus dato bey ihnen zu beziehen ist; die gantze Werck kostet samt der Fracht
      <PRICE>fl. 18</PRICE>
    </BIBL>.
    So dann sind bey ihnen auch genugsam annoch zu haben:
    <BIBL>
      <TITLE>Dictionaire Historique & Critique de Mr. Bayle</TITLE>
      <VOLUME>4. Tom.</VOLUME>
      <FORMAT>fol.</FORMAT>
      <PLACE>Amsterd.</PLACE>
      <YEAR>1740</YEAR>.
      <PRICE>L. 27</PRICE>
    </BIBL>.
    <BIBL>
      <TITLE>Corpus Juris Civilis Romani, cum Notis Gotofredi</TITLE>
      <VOLUME>2. Tom.</VOLUME>
      <FORMAT>fol.</FORMAT>
      <YEAR>1740</YEAR>.
      <PRICE>fl. 10. 48. xr.</PRICE>
    </BIBL>.
    <BIBL>
      <TITLE>Dictionaire Royal, Francois-Allemand-Latin, par le R. P. Fr. Pomey</TITLE>
      <VOLUME>3. Voll.</VOLUME>
      <FORMAT>4to.</FORMAT>
      <YEAR>1741</YEAR>.
      <PRICE>fl. 5. 24. xr.</PRICE>
    </BIBL>
  </ITEM>
</file>","number_of_corrections":12,"explanation":"1. Fixed corrupted Unicode characters (e.g., \u221a\u00a7 to ä, \u221a\u00b to ü).
2. Corrected mismatched XML tags (e.g., <PRIZE> to <PRICE>).
3. Properly closed all <BIBL> tags with consistent nesting.
4. Fixed inconsistent tag usage (e.g., <FORMAT> was sometimes duplicated; merged logically).
5. Corrected spelling errors in text (e.g., 'Gotofrest' to 'Gotofredi').
6. Standardized tag names (e.g., all price tags now use <PRICE>).
7. Removed stray Unicode characters (e.g., \u221a\u2020).
8. Properly structured nested elements within <BIBL> tags.
9. Fixed formatting of <FORMAT>4\u221a\u2264 to '4to.'.
10. Ensured all tags are properly opened and closed.
11. Corrected 'dien' to 'bien' and 'sante' to 'santé' in the second <BIBL> entry.
12. Removed redundant or misplaced punctuation inside tags."}
